#. type: Title =
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Regions: Feathering\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:5
msgid "[5 of 10](Regions-Adding_Point.html)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:11
msgid ""
"Every region in LightZone has a *feathering area* that is marked by an inner "
"line that matches the contour of the region. Inside the inner line, the tool "
"for the region has 100% effect; outside the outer line, the tool has 0% "
"effect. In between, the tool's effect is smoothly \"feathered\" from 0 to "
"100%."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** This feathering is reversed if the region has been\n"
"[inverted](Regions-Inverting.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "To adjust the size of the feathering area of a region:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:28
msgid ""
"Click the Regions button in the [tool bar](Tools-Controls.html).  (The "
"region kind buttons will appear to the right of the tool bar and the regions "
"for the tool will become visible on your photo.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:28
msgid ""
"![image](images/Region-Feather.png) Double-click the region whose feathering "
"area you want to adjust. (The control points and the inner line will become "
"visible.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:28
msgid ""
"Drag the inner line out or in to increase or decrease the size of the "
"feathering area."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4.  '
#: Regions-Feathering.markdown.txt:28
msgid ""
"When done, you can either click anywhere outside the region, or press either "
"the **return** or **esc** (escape) key."
msgstr ""
